## Acceptance Criteria

- [x] TTLCache class with thread-safe get/set/clear
- [x] Azure pricing API fetched with 1-hour TTL cache
- [x] Default to API, fallback to embedded with log warning
- [x] Source citations in pricing data comments
- [x] Unit tests for caching layer
- [x] All existing tests pass

---

## Implementation
### Changes Made
- src/burnt/core/cache.py - New TTLCache class (thread-safe, 3600s default TTL)
- src/burnt/core/config.py - Added cache_ttl_seconds (3600.0 default), changed pricing_source default to "api"
- src/burnt/core/instances.py - Added pricing cache, fetch_azure_pricing(), get_fresh_pricing()
- tests/unit/test_instances.py - Added TestTTLCache and TestGetFreshPricing tests

### Implementation Notes
- Default behavior: try API first, fallback to embedded with WARNING log
- pricing_source="embedded" uses only hardcoded catalog (no API calls)
- pricing_source="api" (default) tries API, falls back on failure

### Verification Results
- Tests: 329 passed
- Lint: pass

